# Amendment A — Project Preservation Rules

> This amendment overrides every future design document in this Design Bible.

---

# Core Principle

Portfolio V3 is an enhancement project.

It is **NOT** a redesign project.

The objective is to preserve the existing identity while significantly increasing immersion, polish, and interaction quality.

Every implementation must respect the existing product before introducing new features.

---

# Preservation Rule 01 — Content is Sacred

The portfolio exists to showcase work.

Content always has higher priority than visual effects.

Do not rewrite, replace, reorder, simplify, or redesign the existing content unless explicitly requested.

This includes, but is not limited to:

* Hero copy
* About section
* Skills
* Timeline
* Experience
* Projects
* Certifications
* Contact information
* Resume links
* Social links
* SEO metadata

Animations may support the content.

They must never replace it.

---

# Preservation Rule 02 — Analytics are Untouchable

The existing analytics implementation must remain exactly as it is.

Do not remove analytics.

Do not replace analytics.

Do not modify event tracking.

Do not rename tracking events.

Do not introduce breaking changes.

Any animation or interaction introduced into the portfolio must remain compatible with the existing analytics system.

Analytics must continue collecting data exactly as before.

---

# Preservation Rule 03 — Terminal Mode is the Identity

The terminal command system is the signature feature of this portfolio.

It is considered part of the product identity.

Therefore:

Do not redesign it.

Do not simplify it.

Do not replace it with buttons.

Do not replace it with toggles.

Do not hide it.

Do not automate it.

Do not remove commands.

Do not change its personality.

Developer Mode and Hacker Mode must continue switching exactly through the existing terminal interaction.

The implementation may be optimized internally if necessary, but the user experience must remain unchanged.

---

# Preservation Rule 04 — Existing Features Come First

Before adding any new feature:

Verify that all existing features continue functioning exactly as before.

No regression is acceptable.

If a new effect breaks an existing interaction,

the new effect must be removed.

---

# Preservation Rule 05 — Progressive Enhancement

Every enhancement should be additive.

Nothing currently working should be sacrificed.

The visitor should feel:

"The portfolio became richer."

Never:

"The portfolio became different."

---

# Preservation Rule 06 — Respect Existing Architecture

Whenever possible,

extend existing components instead of replacing them.

Avoid unnecessary rewrites.

Prefer composition over replacement.

Preserve proven logic.

Improve implementation quality without changing product behavior.

---

# Final Rule

The goal of Portfolio V3 is not to build a new portfolio.

The goal is to make the current portfolio feel like the best possible version of itself.
